    "(2.5)Following common nomenclature, we call \"in\" and \"out\" states those prepared using exclusively operations in the past or future, namely|m • • • 1⟩ in ≡ a † m • • • a † 1 |0⟩ and |m • • • 1⟩ out ≡ b † m • • • b † 1 |0⟩.",
    "(2.6)The overlap between \"in\" and \"out\" states is given by matrix elements of S. That is,out ⟨m+n • • • m+1|m • • • 1⟩ in = ⟨0|b m+n • • • b m+1 a † m • • • a † 1 |0⟩ = ⟨0|a m+n • • • a m+1 S a † m • • • a † 1 |0⟩ ≡ ⟨m+n • • • m+1|S|m • • • 1⟩, (2.7)where we have used both rules (2.2) and (2.3).",
